FOUNDRY IAM

SCIM 2.0 PROVISIONING EXTENSION

Feature Specification — Phase 2



Document Type

Feature Extension Spec

Phase

Phase 2 — Post-MVP

Estimated Build

7–10 engineering days

Trigger

Enterprise customer with HR/IdP automated provisioning



This document specifies the SCIM 2.0 provisioning extension. SCIM (System for Cross-domain Identity Management) enables enterprise customers to automatically sync users and groups from their HR system (Workday, BambooHR) or Identity Provider (Okta, Azure AD) into Foundry IAM — without manual user management. An engineer receiving only this document should be able to implement the feature without access to other Foundry IAM specifications.



SECTION 1

What SCIM Is and Why It Matters



1.1 Protocol Overview

SCIM 2.0 (RFC 7643 + RFC 7644) is a REST + JSON protocol for automating user provisioning and deprovisioning between systems. Instead of an admin manually creating users in Foundry IAM, an enterprise's Identity Provider (Okta, Azure AD) pushes user creates, updates, and deletes directly to our SCIM endpoint.

In the Foundry IAM context, Foundry IAM is the SCIM Service Provider (server). The enterprise's IdP is the SCIM Client (provisioner). When an employee joins the company, their HR system tells Okta, Okta tells Foundry IAM via SCIM, and the user appears in the correct Keycloak realm automatically.

1.2 The Business Case — Why This Is an Enterprise Deal-Maker

Use Case

Value

Employee onboarding

New hire added in Workday → synced to Okta → pushed via SCIM to Foundry IAM → user exists in correct realm and groups before day one. Zero manual steps.

Employee offboarding

Employee terminated in HR system → SCIM DELETE call → user disabled in Keycloak within minutes. No zombie accounts. Compliance requirement met.

Group sync

Department changes in IdP automatically update Keycloak groups → role assignments stay accurate without admin intervention.

Compliance

SOC 2, ISO 27001, and HIPAA all require automated deprovisioning. Manual processes fail audits. SCIM is the standard answer.

Scale

An enterprise with 10,000 employees cannot onboard via portal invites. SCIM or nothing.

