SECTION 2

Architecture — Where SCIM Lives



2.1 New Service: SCIM Gateway

SCIM is implemented as a new lightweight service — the SCIM Gateway — rather than adding SCIM endpoints to the existing control plane API. This keeps concerns separated: the control plane API handles tenant management and billing; the SCIM Gateway handles user provisioning protocol.

Property

Value

Service name

scim

Port (local dev)

3001

Technology

Node.js 20 + Express + TypeScript

Auth

Bearer token per workspace SCIM configuration (not portal JWT)

Database

Reads/writes control_plane schema. Does NOT have its own schema.

Keycloak access

Direct Keycloak Admin REST API (same as control plane API)

New folder

foundry-iam/scim/ (added to monorepo alongside existing services)

2.2 Request Flow — Okta pushes a new user

Okta (SCIM Client)

  POST https://api.foundry-iam.com/scim/v2/wsp_c91b12/Users

  Authorization: Bearer scim_token_xyz

  Content-Type: application/scim+json

  { "userName": "jane@acme.com", "name": { "givenName": "Jane", ... }, "active": true }

  ↓

SCIM Gateway

  1. Validate Bearer token → map to workspace_id (wsp_c91b12)

  2. Parse SCIM User resource

  3. Map SCIM attributes → Keycloak user attributes

  4. POST /admin/realms/tnt_2f8a1d/users (Keycloak Admin API)

  5. Assign groups from SCIM groups claim

  6. Write scim_user record to control_plane DB (SCIM ID ↔ Keycloak user ID)

  7. Return SCIM User resource with id, meta.location

  ↓

Okta stores SCIM ID for future updates/deletes

2.3 URL Structure — Workspace-Scoped SCIM Endpoints

Each workspace gets its own SCIM base URL. This enforces tenant isolation at the URL level and allows different SCIM credentials per workspace.

Base URL pattern: https://api.foundry-iam.com/scim/v2/{workspace_id}/

Examples:

  https://api.foundry-iam.com/scim/v2/wsp_c91b12/Users

  https://api.foundry-iam.com/scim/v2/wsp_c91b12/Groups

  https://api.foundry-iam.com/scim/v2/wsp_c91b12/ServiceProviderConfig

  https://api.foundry-iam.com/scim/v2/wsp_c91b12/Schemas

Each workspace has a unique SCIM Bearer token.

Token is generated by the control plane and stored hashed in the DB.

Token rotation is available via the portal.



