SECTION 4

SCIM Attribute Mapping



SCIM uses a standard User schema (RFC 7643). Keycloak uses its own attribute model. The SCIM Gateway must translate between them in both directions (inbound provisioning and outbound reads).

4.1 Default User Attribute Mapping

SCIM Attribute

Keycloak Attribute

Notes

userName

username

Used as login name. Typically email address.

name.givenName

firstName

name.familyName

lastName

emails[primary].value

email

Primary email

active

enabled

false → user disabled in Keycloak (cannot login)

externalId

attributes.scim_external_id

Stored as user attribute

id (SCIM)

— (control plane scim_users.id)

Not stored on KC user; mapped via scim_users table

groups

group membership

POST to /admin/realms/{r}/users/{id}/groups/{groupId}

phoneNumbers[primary].value

attributes.phoneNumber

Stored as KC user attribute

title

attributes.title

Stored as KC user attribute

department

attributes.department

organization

attributes.organization

4.2 Custom Attribute Mapping (user_attribute_mappings column)

Tenants can override or extend the default mapping. Stored as JSONB in scim_configurations.

// Example: map custom SCIM enterprise extension to KC attributes

{

  "urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:extension:enterprise:2.0:User:employeeNumber": "attributes.employeeId",

  "urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:extension:enterprise:2.0:User:costCenter": "attributes.costCenter",

  "urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:extension:enterprise:2.0:User:division": "attributes.division"

}

4.3 SCIM User Resource — Canonical Shape

{

  "schemas": ["urn:ietf:params:scim:schemas:core:2.0:User"],

  "id": "usr_scim_9a1b2c",

  "externalId": "okta-user-id-12345",

  "userName": "jane.doe@acme.com",

  "name": {

    "formatted": "Jane Doe",

    "givenName": "Jane",

    "familyName": "Doe"

  },

  "emails": [{ "value": "jane.doe@acme.com", "primary": true, "type": "work" }],

  "active": true,

  "groups": [

    { "value": "grp_engineering", "display": "Engineering", "$ref": ".../Groups/grp_engineering" }

  ],

  "meta": {

    "resourceType": "User",

    "created": "2026-02-28T12:00:00Z",

    "lastModified": "2026-02-28T12:00:00Z",

    "location": "https://api.foundry-iam.com/scim/v2/wsp_c91b12/Users/usr_scim_9a1b2c"

  }

}



SECTION 5

Control Plane API — New Endpoints (SCIM Management)



These endpoints are added to the existing control plane API (port 3000). They allow tenant admins to configure and manage the SCIM integration from the portal. They are separate from the SCIM protocol endpoints (port 3001) which are called by the IdP.

Method

Path

Description

POST

/v1/workspaces/:id/scim/enable

Enable SCIM for workspace + generate Bearer token (shown once)

