Step-by-step guides for Okta, Azure AD, Google Workspace

7.2 SCIM Config Page — UX Spec

Disabled state: Large 'Enable SCIM Provisioning' button with a one-sentence explainer. Link to setup guide.

On enable: Show modal warning that the token will only appear once. Require checkbox confirmation. Display token in a masked input with copy button and 'I have saved this token' confirmation before closing modal.

Enabled state: Status badge (green Active). Base URL + token prefix displayed with copy button for base URL. 'Rotate Token' button (with same once-shown flow). 'Disable SCIM' danger button.

Settings section: deprovision_action toggle (Disable / Delete, with warning on Delete). sync_groups toggle. allowed_operations multi-checkbox.

7.3 Setup Guide Content (SCIMSetup.tsx)

Step-by-step instructions per IdP, with screenshots described for implementation. These instructions must be accurate — incorrect setup guide is the #1 source of SCIM support tickets.

IdP

Key Steps

Okta

Admin → Applications → Provisioning → Enable API integration → Enter Base URL + Bearer token → Test connection → Enable Create/Update/Deactivate

Azure AD / Entra ID

Enterprise Apps → Provisioning → Automatic → Tenant URL = Base URL → Secret Token = Bearer token → Test connection → Start provisioning

Google Workspace

Admin SDK provisioning → SCIM configuration → endpoint URL → authentication → attribute mapping

OneLogin

Administration → Provisioning → SCIM connector → URL + Bearer token → attribute mapping → enable

Generic SCIM 2.0

Configure SCIM 2.0 endpoint with Bearer token auth. Base URL, /Users, /Groups. Filter support: userName eq, externalId eq.



