8.1 Recommended Test Tooling

Tool

Purpose

Okta Developer Account

Free. Configure SCIM provisioning against local ngrok tunnel. Most realistic test.

ngrok

Expose local SCIM gateway (port 3001) to internet for IdP testing. Required for Okta/Azure AD integration tests.

scim2-compliance-suite (npm)

Run against your SCIM implementation to check RFC 7644 compliance.

Postman SCIM collection

Build a Postman collection covering all operations. Use as regression suite.

Azure AD Free Tier

Free Azure AD tenant supports SCIM provisioning to custom apps for testing.



SECTION 9

Implementation Plan — 10 Days



Day

Focus

Deliverable

Day 1

Research + DB setup

All 3 new tables migrated. Keycloak Admin API tested for user create/update/disable. RFC 7644 read and summarised.

Day 2

SCIM Gateway scaffold + auth

New scim/ folder in monorepo. Express app running on port 3001. Auth middleware working with test token.

Day 3

ServiceProviderConfig + Schemas + User GET

Static endpoints implemented. GET /Users with pagination working. GET /Users/:id working.

Day 4

User CREATE + filter support

POST /Users provisions user in Keycloak. Filter query parsing implemented (userName eq, externalId eq).

Day 5

User UPDATE (PUT + PATCH) + DELETE

Full replace (PUT), partial update (PATCH), and DELETE with deprovision_action logic.

Day 6

Groups — full CRUD

GET, POST, PATCH (add/remove members), DELETE for Groups. KC group sync working.

Day 7

Control plane endpoints

POST enable, GET config, PATCH config, POST token/rotate, GET users, GET logs — all wired to DB and SCIM gateway.

Day 8

Portal UI — config + setup guide

SCIMConfig.tsx and SCIMSetup.tsx complete. Token shown-once flow working.

Day 9

Portal UI — users + logs + integration tests

SCIMUsers and SCIMLogs pages. End-to-end test with Okta Developer account via ngrok.

Day 10

Test matrix + documentation

All 20 test cases executed. Docs site updated. Okta and Azure AD setup guides validated.

Compliance Note

SCIM DELETE must default to DISABLE, not hard delete. Enterprise customers audit user deletion. Hard deletes lose audit history. Make deprovision_action=disable the default and require explicit configuration change to enable hard deletes.



End of SCIM 2.0 Provisioning Extension Specification
